  "text": "Given the vocabulary differences between KSs and Tweets, one of the challenges faced by these models is the frequent usage of grammatically incorrect English in Microposts. Due to the restricted size of short messages, entities such as country names (e.g. nkorea) are often abbreviated, as in the following Tweet: \"nkorea prepared nuclear weapons holy war south official tells state media usa\". These irregularities mean that current annotation services (including OpenCalais API) will ignore these entities, and therefore no semantic information will be exploited for these entities by the TC system. A possible solution to address these challenges is to apply lexical normalisers especially developed for Tweets ( [CITATION_1] ) to normalise these words to standard English terms.",
